18 Section 4. Section 70-25-204, MCA, is amended to read:
19 "70-25-204. Wrongful withholding of security deposit -- action. (1) A person who wrongfully
20 withholds a residential property security deposit or any portion of the deposit is liable in damages to the tenant
21 in a civil action for an amount equal to the sum determined to have been wrongfully withheld or deducted. The
22 attorney fees may be awarded to the prevailing party at the discretion of the court. The burden of proof of
23 damages caused by the tenant to the leasehold premises is on the landlord.
24 (2) An action may not be maintained by a tenant for any amount wrongfully withheld or deducted
